==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|acutus|acūtus|sharp|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|acuo|acuō|sharpen, make sharp|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-acute.ogg|Audio (US)}}

*: {{rhymes|uːt}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|'''more acute''' or '''[[acuter]]'''|'''most acute''' or '''[[acutest]]'''}}

# {{medicine}} Sudden [[onset]], does not define severity or duration.
#: '' '''acute''' onset of illness.''
#: '' '''acute''' onset of action.''
# [[urgent|Urgent]].
#: ''His need for medical attention was '''acute'''''.''
# [[quick|Quick]].
#: ''It was an '''acute''' event.''

